&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/panama-reforestation-visa/" ref="nofollow">Panama Reforestation Visa</a></span><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">.</span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">What is the cost of living in Panama?</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">The cost depends on the place you&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/where-do-expats-live-in-panama/" ref="nofollow">Live in Panama</a></span><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">. It is a lot less expensive to live where mostly working Panamanian people live. An average lifestyle for a couple on a budget, can cost under $1,000 and up to $3,500 to live comfortably in a prime area for expats with travel and entertainment.</span></span></span></p><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://alittleadrift.com/cost-of-living/panama/#costs" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Compare with other countries at</a></span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">What’s the average salary for experienced Professionals in Panama?</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Average gross salary in Panama is&nbsp;</span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);">US $65,000</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);"> Average net salary is&nbsp;</span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);">US $50,000</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);"> The most frequent gross salary is&nbsp;</span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);">US $30,000</span></span></span></strong></p><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://www.averagesalarysurvey.com/panama" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Compare it with other countries at</a></span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);">Excellent Ownership opportunities for a Profitable Business</span></span></span></strong></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">With no mandatory reporting requirements for foreign income, Business opportunities are always popping up around the Panama Canal, the Free Zone, the busiest port in the world and the Latin American Banking Center that is home to more than 5,000 financial services. Foreigners living in Panama keep on making international deals because millions of business people are always visiting Panama for many different reasons.&nbsp;</span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://offshoreww.com/international-economy" ref="nofollow">LEARN MORE</a></span></span></span></strong></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);">Is it safe to live in Panama?</span></span></span></strong></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Panama is a safe country. The army has been replaced by a police force that keeps crime to a minimum in most areas. If you are a newcomer, you should obviously take precaution with who you associate and where you visit. Don’t go to the red light district at night flashing your wallet and jewelry if you are alone. In the poorer neighborhoods, you should be wary of pickpockets in crowded areas after dark.</span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Quality Healthcare with low cost Medical Insurance</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Public hospitals and clinics that are administrated by the Ministry of Health are designed to serve the poor and are almost free because of the very low cost. A notch up are the hospitals that are run by the social security system and cater to working Panamanians who are registered and get free care. Foreigners can also go and pay modest fees. Finally, there is a Private system of offices, clinics and private hospitals. Some of these hospitals are top notch with doctors associated with the top North American hospital. Even these hospitals are very affordable compared to healthcare costs in Europe and North America. Health insurance is offered at a small fraction of the costs of the North American insurance plans.</span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Different Climates for everyone’s Choice</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">The climate in the Capital is not so desirable but a short drive away you can live in a cool mountain village, a ranch in the Valley or a beachfront community. Drive a bit further and you can go from the Pacific to the Atlantic Ocean in less than a short 100 kms drive on a 4-lane highway. Find the best place that you’d want to&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/where-do-expats-live-in-panama/" ref="nofollow">Live in Panama</a></span></span></span></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Luxury Living in Panama is still possible on a small budget</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">In Panama you can buy a house in a village for $7,000 or a Mansion for $25,000,000 all within a 35 kms radius. The common denominator is that everyone wants to have fun. There are many exclusive areas frequented by international billionaires and celebrities that go home with helicopters but mostly foreigners have fun in private parties, three entertainment districts and concert hall that brings international singers like Marc Anthony and Justin Bieber. The local&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://www.internations.org/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Internations&nbsp;</a></span><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">hosts 3 to 4 events per week and boasts a membership of people living in Panama but originate from 145 countries. There are hundreds of such groups and many international Conventions and Trade Fairs. </span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(128, 26, 31);"><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/living-in-panama/" ref="nofollow">LEARN MORE</a></span></span></span></strong></p><h1 style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 16pxpx"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">CONCLUSION</span></span></span></h1><p><span style="font-family: segoe ui, frutiger, frutiger linotype, dejavu sans, helvetica neue, arial, sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 20.8px"><span style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64);">Qualify for the Panama Second Passport with a Citizenship Program that starts by investing as little as $5,000 in your own profitable business. You can visit for only a week and then go back home. If you prefer, stay in Panama and run a profitable business without paying taxes on income generated from outside Panama. Combining the cost effective immigration programs with the business infrastructure, luxury lifestyle on a budget, beaches, mountains, healthcare, safety and top class amenities has made Panama the top choice for the easiest Second Passport while generating tax free profits through Panama’s Citizenship Program</span></span></span></p>', '2020-11-02 17:32:34.911', NULL, NULL, 'why-panama-has-the-easiest-citizenship-program', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'en');
