hose identity is unknown or unconfirmed. Secondly, such names are also often used to refer to a hypothetical "</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">everyman</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" in other contexts, in a manner similar to "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">John Q. Public</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" or "Joe Public". There are many variants to the above names, including "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">John Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Richard Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Jane Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" and "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Baby Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Janie Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" or "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Johnny Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" (for children).</span></span></span></span></p><table><tbody><tr><th><p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/John_and_Jane_Doe_Headstones.jpg/220px-John_and_Jane_Doe_Headstones.jpg" alt="" title="" width="497" height="208" data-display="inline"></p></th><th><p><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12.3704px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">Four headstones marking the single grave of four unknown people in the Pima County Cemetery,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Tucson</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Arizona</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">United States</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">. They are called "John Doe" or "Jane Doe" followed by a number sign (#) and a number. In the same cemetery, the murdered&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Deanna Criswell</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">&nbsp;was called "Jane Doe 19" for 27 years until she was genetically identified in 2015 by her relatives with help from&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">the FBI</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">The Doe Network</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">.</span></span></span></span></p></th></tr></tbody></table><h3 style="line-height: 130%;"><span style="font-family: Arial Black"><span style="font-size: 20px"><span style="color: #000000;">1988 John Doe identified</span></span></span></h3><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_M9Qi-dP__k" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe><p></p><p>Well done!</p>', '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 'do-you-know-whom-is-john-or-jane-doe', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://45.82.75.51:8080/do-you-know-whom-is-john-or-jane-doe', NULL, 16, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '1eo313qcj5', 'en');
INSERT INTO "blogs"("blog_id", "user_id", "caption", "published", "created_on", "picture_id", "content", "updated_on", "primary_tag", "secondary_tag", "slug", "primary_category", "secondary_category", "description", "url", "snippet", "author_id", "refering_id", "related_id", "note", "like", "comment", "linked_id", "lang") VALUES ('1eodeaok59', 16, 'NEW Living in Panama - a Booming Metropolis Close to Beaches', 'f', '2020-11-30 20:43:29.288', NULL, '<h3 data-indent="1" style="text-align: center;line-height: 140%;"><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Why should I move to Panama?</span></span></span></strong></h3><p></p><p><a href="#lifestyle" ref="nofollow">Lifestyle</a></p><p><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2876&amp;action=edit#Tax-Haven" ref="nofollow">Tax Haven</a></p><p><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2876&amp;action=edit#Entertainment-and-Fun" ref="nofollow">Entertainment and Fun </a><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2876&amp;action=edit#Business-and-Economy" ref="nofollow">Business and Economy </a><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2876&amp;action=edit#Travel-and-Transportation" ref="nofollow">Travel and Transportation </a><a href="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=2876&amp;action=edit#exploration-and-discovery" ref="nofollow">Exploration and Discovery</a></p><h3>Living in Panama offers all these benefits:</h3><h2><span id="#lifestyle">Lifestyle</span></h2><p><img src="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/pexels-asad-photo-maldives-1024960-1024x683.jpg" alt="This image has an empty alt attribute; its file name is pexels-asad-photo-maldives-1024960-1024x683.jpg" title="" data-display="inline"></p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Many Multicultural Communities</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> People of all races and nationalities are&nbsp;living in Panama&nbsp;without having any cultural friction.&nbsp;The country is a melting pot of cultures and embraces its diversity with pride.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Outstanding Health Care</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Foreign residents&nbsp;living in Panama&nbsp;don’t worry much about health care because Panama has world class medical and alternative health care facilities.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Residential Options for all Price Points</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Those moving to Panama find many choices of residential accommodations that fit every budget.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Libertarian Society</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> One of the many benefits of moving to Panama is feeling the freedom of a libertarian society where everything goes as long as it does not infringe upon the rights of others.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Population that is Friendly to Foreigners</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Moving to Panama is suitable for individuals who want to meet fun loving and easy-going locals. Panamanians&nbsp;are very welcoming to tourists and foreigners.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Diverse Climate</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Panama offers a variety of city, beach, rural and mountain climates within a radius of 100 kilometers.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Public and Private Schools</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> There is a large network of free public schools. Starting for around 300 USD per month, there are also many affordable private schools that are offering primary and secondary education in&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.javier.edu/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Spanish</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.stmarypanama.com/StMary2016/StMary2016.html" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">English</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.colegioalemannk.org/es" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">German</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://lfpanama.edu.pa/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">French</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Escuela_Japonesa_de_Panam%C3%A1" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Japanese</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="https://www.ccchp-isys.edu.pa/index.php/informacion-general" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Mandarin</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.aiap.edu.pa/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Arabic</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.institutoatenea.edu.pa/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Greek</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">. Foreigners who are living in Panama with their children, find this to be a very important factor for the well-being of the whole family unit. No other country offers such a huge variety of educational options.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">University and Post Graduate Education</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Panama has over 100&nbsp;</span><span style="color: rgb(0, 115, 170);"><a href="http://www.4icu.org/pa/" target="_blank" ref="nofollow noopener noreferrer">universities</a></span><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">&nbsp;that welcome foreigners with a special&nbsp;Panama Visa for students. Many of these Institutions have international affiliations leading to post-graduate programs in Europe and North America. After living in Panama for some time, some foreign students decide to marry their sweetheart, get a job and live in Panama permanently.</span></span></span></p></li></ul><h3 style="text-align: center;line-height: 140%;"><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Tax Haven</span></span></span></strong></h3><p><img src="https://panama-visa.offshoreww.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/pexels-pixabay-2145-1024x682.jpg" alt="This image has an empty alt attribute; its file name is pexels-pixabay-2145-1024x682.jpg" title="" data-display="inline"></p><p></p><ul><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Low Tax Status at Home</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Foreign residents with a Panama Retirement Visa&nbsp;pay no taxes&nbsp;and&nbsp;enjoy a low tax status in their country of citizenship.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">Tax-Free Foreign Income</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Local and foreign residents with a&nbsp;Panama Visa&nbsp;can&nbsp;receive&nbsp;tax-free foreign income.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">No Reporting Requirements</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Businesses are moving to Panama to form&nbsp;corporations&nbsp;and&nbsp;foundations&nbsp;and&nbsp;avoid having to file tax returns.</span></span></span></p></li><li><p><strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);">High Local Income with Low Taxes</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: Noto Serif"><span style="font-size: 16px"><span style="color: rgb(30, 30, 30);"> Individuals with a&nbsp;Panama Visa&nbsp;have many opportunities to generate high local income. The best part is that they pay low taxes and don’t need much capital because they qualify for local financing.</span></span></span></p></li></ul><p></p>', '1970-01-01 00:00:00', NULL, NULL, 'new-living-in-panama-a-booming-metropolis-close-to-beaches', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://45.82.75.51:8080/new-living-in-panama-a-booming-metropolis-close-to-beaches', NULL, 16, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, NULL, 'es');
INSERT INTO "blogs"("blog_id", "user_id", "caption", "published", "created_on", "picture_id", "content", "updated_on", "primary_tag", "secondary_tag", "slug", "primary_category", "secondary_category", "description", "url", "snippet", "author_id", "refering_id", "related_id", "note", "like", "comment", "linked_id", "lang") VALUES ('1eo313qcj5', 16, 'Do you know who are John and Jane Doe?', 't', '2020-11-26 19:40:05.917', NULL, '<p><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">"</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">John Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" (for males) and "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Jane Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" (for females) are&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">multiple-use names</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp;that are used when the true name of a person is unknown or is being intentionally concealed.&nbsp;In the context of&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">law enforcement in the United States</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">, such names are often used to refer to a&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">corpse</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp;whose identity is unknown or unconfirmed. Secondly, such names are also often used to refer to a hypothetical "</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">everyman</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" in other contexts, in a manner similar to "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">John Q. Public</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" or "Joe Public". There are many variants to the above names, including "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">John Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Richard Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Jane Roe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" and "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Baby Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">", "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Janie Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" or "</span></span></span></span><strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);">Johnny Doe</span></span></span></strong><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 14px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">" (for children).</span></span></span></span></p><table><tbody><tr><th><p><img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/John_and_Jane_Doe_Headstones.jpg/220px-John_and_Jane_Doe_Headstones.jpg" alt="" title="" width="497" height="208" data-display="inline"></p></th><th><p><span style="font-family: sans-serif"><span style="font-size: 12.3704px"><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">Four headstones marking the single grave of four unknown people in the Pima County Cemetery,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Tucson</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Arizona</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">,&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">United States</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">. They are called "John Doe" or "Jane Doe" followed by a number sign (#) and a number. In the same cemetery, the murdered&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">Deanna Criswell</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">&nbsp;was called "Jane Doe 19" for 27 years until she was genetically identified in 2015 by her relatives with help from&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">the FBI</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">&nbsp;and&nbsp;</span></span><span style="color: rgb(11, 0, 128);">The Doe Network</span><span style="color: rgb(32, 33, 34);"><span style="background-color: rgb(248, 249, 250);">.</span></span></span></span></p></th></tr></tbody></table><h3 style="line-height: 130%;"><span style="font-family: Arial Black"><span style="font-size: 20px"><span style="color: #000000;">1988 John Doe identified</span></span></span></h3><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_M9Qi-dP__k" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="true"></iframe><p></p>', '2020-11-30 00:00:00', 17, NULL, 'do-you-know-who-are-john-and-jane-doe-1eo3164vpk', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'http://45.82.75.51:8080/do-you-know-who-are-john-and-jane-doe-1eo3164vpk', NULL, 16, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 0, '1eo309mc7j', 'es');
